[August 25 in 1609, in Kangneung]

6
00:01:19,039 --> 00:01:20,910
Stop crying.

7
00:01:21,280 --> 00:01:24,780
It’s so pathetic that

8
00:01:24,780 --> 00:01:29,050
our lady was bullied like this.

9
00:01:28,330 --> 00:01:34,410
[Widow: the young girl loses her husband
before the wedding.]

10
00:01:30,460 --> 00:01:33,520
She is only 15 years old.

11
00:01:33,520 --> 00:01:39,150
She even didn’t see her husband,
but now becomes a widow.

12
00:01:39,150 --> 00:01:41,780
What a poor girl!

13
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:19,720
Anybody help!

14
00:02:19,720 --> 00:02:21,710
Help me out!

15
00:02:21,710 --> 00:02:23,370
Help me out!

16
00:05:28,770 --> 00:05:31,430
In the year 1609,

17
00:05:31,750 --> 00:05:35,730
as recorded in the memoir of Joseon Dynasty,

18
00:05:35,730 --> 00:05:39,520
a UFO was witnessed at the same moment.

19
00:05:40,210 --> 00:05:44,900
It’s the UFO that brought me to Joseon.

20
00:05:44,900 --> 00:05:50,800
The planet I lived is named KMT184.05.

21
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:53,750
It has very similar environment to the earth.

22
00:05:54,159 --> 00:05:57,470
I came from that planet.

23
00:06:03,660 --> 00:06:06,400
From Joseon Dynasty till today,

24
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:08,620
Hanyang became Seoul,

25
00:06:08,620 --> 00:06:11,080
and I’ve lived here for over 400 years.

26
00:06:14,250 --> 00:06:18,980
From magnetic and gravity to water,

27
00:06:18,980 --> 00:06:22,400
now I adapt myself well to the life on Earth.

28
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:27,940
My senses are seven times better than earthmen.

29
00:06:27,940 --> 00:06:33,270
So I can see and hear things I don't want to.

30
00:06:45,540 --> 00:06:48,350
There is no special limit to my food,

31
00:06:48,350 --> 00:06:51,860
but it can’t mix with earthmen’s saliva or blood.

32
00:06:51,860 --> 00:06:53,280
So…

33
00:06:53,280 --> 00:06:55,310
I have every meal all by myself.

34
00:07:02,570 --> 00:07:04,050
Hey!

35
00:07:04,320 --> 00:07:05,920
Give back my bag!

36
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:08,040
The robber! What should I do?

37
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:11,110
Anyone help? Gosh!

38
00:07:11,840 --> 00:07:15,070
Help! Please help me!

39
00:07:15,910 --> 00:07:17,730
Why didn’t I help her?

40
00:07:17,730 --> 00:07:22,070
My involvement in their life is meaningless.

41
00:07:22,070 --> 00:07:24,140
It’s not my intention.

42
00:07:24,140 --> 00:07:28,420
Just like being here from another planet,

43
00:07:28,420 --> 00:07:33,850
things will happen, whether you want it or not.

44
00:07:34,950 --> 00:07:40,800
It’s named “destiny” by earthmen.

45
00:07:59,020 --> 00:08:01,330
[‘Comet of the century’ is brighter
than the Mid-autumn moon.]

46
00:08:03,030 --> 00:08:06,930
[It can be seen on earth three months later.]

47
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:24,290
My new destiny begins.

48
00:08:24,290 --> 00:08:28,830
The comet I’ve been waiting for is getting near.

49
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:35,190
I can return to my comet in three months.

50
00:08:51,410 --> 00:08:55,150
[My Love from the Star Record 1]

51
00:09:14,140 --> 00:09:15,390
Song-yi,

52
00:09:15,390 --> 00:09:17,600
here is your coffee.

53
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:20,080
Mocha?

54
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:22,610
Yes, as you asked.

55
00:09:22,610 --> 00:09:24,040
Excuse me.

56
00:09:36,390 --> 00:09:38,140
It’s yours now.

57
00:09:38,140 --> 00:09:39,960
Thank you.

58
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:43,310
But I bought it from somewhere far away.

59
00:09:43,310 --> 00:09:45,880
Mocha has high calories, you know?

60
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:49,190
I don't want to waste time to burn calories.

61
00:09:49,190 --> 00:09:52,670
You are really good at self-management.

62
00:09:52,670 --> 00:09:54,420
Sure I am.

63
00:09:54,420 --> 00:09:55,340
Did you move everything there?

64
00:09:55,340 --> 00:09:56,690
Of course.

65
00:09:56,690 --> 00:09:59,810
I didn’t leave until they finished cleaning.

66
00:10:01,930 --> 00:10:02,940
Song-yi,

67
00:10:03,460 --> 00:10:05,000
what are you doing?

68
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,790
Communicating with fans.

69
00:10:06,790 --> 00:10:08,760
SNS again?

70
00:10:08,760 --> 00:10:10,900
What did you post?

71
00:10:12,970 --> 00:10:16,330
Sweet Mocha is perfect for a tiring afternoon.

72
00:10:16,330 --> 00:10:20,620
Now I know why Mun Ik-jeom
brought Mocha seeds back secretly.

73
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:22,880
Mun Ik-jeom, thank you.

74
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:26,840
Song-yi, who is Mun Ik-jeom?

75
00:10:26,840 --> 00:10:29,340
Don't you know Mun Ik-jeom who grows Mocha?

76
00:10:29,340 --> 00:10:34,170
He hid the seeds in the pen
and brought them back.

77
00:10:34,170 --> 00:10:36,870
He’s a very smart person.

78
00:10:36,870 --> 00:10:41,250
It’s not Mocha, but cotton seeds.

79
00:10:50,260 --> 00:10:52,010
She takes it as Mocha seeds.

80
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:09,060
I’ve warned you to keep her from Twitter.

81
00:11:09,460 --> 00:11:10,820
What have you done?

82
00:11:10,820 --> 00:11:13,110
Why didn’t you stop her?

83
00:11:13,110 --> 00:11:14,770
You think she would listen to me?

84
00:11:14,770 --> 00:11:16,430
It’s so hard for me.

85
00:11:16,430 --> 00:11:17,630
Is the report reversed?

86
00:11:17,630 --> 00:11:19,390
Almost.

87
00:11:19,390 --> 00:11:21,300
But the trending topics are “Mocha, Mun Ik-jeom”

88
00:11:21,300 --> 00:11:23,980
and “Mun Ik-jeom, Cheon Song-yi”.

89
00:11:25,140 --> 00:11:29,130
She even doesn't know it’s Mocha or cotton.

90
00:11:29,130 --> 00:11:30,360
Mun Ik-jeom would never think

91
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:33,510
of becoming the trending topic this way.

92
00:11:34,010 --> 00:11:37,620
It's a tragedy caused by ignorance.

93
00:11:37,620 --> 00:11:39,820
She is driving me up the wall.

94
00:11:42,810 --> 00:11:46,170
Why did you call me here? I’m tired.

95
00:11:46,170 --> 00:11:47,510
Tired?

96
00:11:48,050 --> 00:11:52,110
But your skin is very good,

97
00:11:52,110 --> 00:11:55,070
as good as for cosmetics ad.

98
00:11:55,070 --> 00:11:56,380
You agree with me, right?

99
00:11:56,380 --> 00:11:58,910
What’s the matter? I’d get back.

100
00:11:58,910 --> 00:12:01,590
Okay. Here is the thing.

101
00:12:03,050 --> 00:12:06,180
Mocha seeds event. You’ve heard it?

102
00:12:07,190 --> 00:12:09,380
I don’t think it deserves to be a topic.

103
00:12:09,380 --> 00:12:10,820
I agree with you.

104
00:12:10,820 --> 00:12:13,230
People always think they know everything.

105
00:12:13,230 --> 00:12:15,760
I didn’t know it’s cotton before yesterday.

106
00:12:15,760 --> 00:12:16,640
Really?

107
00:12:16,640 --> 00:12:18,810
Sure. Of course.

108
00:12:18,810 --> 00:12:23,190
They are finding fault because of jealousy.

109
00:12:23,190 --> 00:12:26,330
I see. That’s people.

110
00:12:26,330 --> 00:12:27,980
Yes. Right.

111
00:12:27,980 --> 00:12:30,570
So don’t lower yourself

112
00:12:30,570 --> 00:12:34,440
by using such things like SNS. Okay?

113
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:35,910
No.

114
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:38,350
Why not?

115
00:12:38,350 --> 00:12:39,840
Any reasons?

116
00:12:39,950 --> 00:12:42,540
I have to talk to people.

117
00:12:42,540 --> 00:12:45,080
You can talk to me.

118
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:46,880
I don’t want to.

119
00:12:48,800 --> 00:12:50,200
Cheon Song-yi,

120
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:50,980
don’t try to...

121
00:12:50,980 --> 00:12:52,380
By the way,

122
00:12:52,380 --> 00:12:55,300
Mr. Park of JK has kept calling me.

123
00:12:55,300 --> 00:12:57,460
Jin-guk? What’s the matter?

124
00:12:57,460 --> 00:12:58,880
I don’t know.

125
00:12:58,880 --> 00:13:02,270
It’s about renewing contract with President An.

126
00:13:02,270 --> 00:13:05,300
JK got a big sum of investment from Japan.

127
00:13:05,300 --> 00:13:07,600
He invited me to join JK.

128
00:13:08,390 --> 00:13:11,030
I heard you’ve been friends for long.

129
00:13:11,030 --> 00:13:12,580
Do you think it’s acceptable?

130
00:13:13,450 --> 00:13:16,410
Park Jin-guk! What do you want?

131
00:13:17,930 --> 00:13:19,760
May I leave now?

132
00:13:20,580 --> 00:13:22,200
Of course. Please.

133
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:23,610
You’d better go back and take a rest.

134
00:13:23,610 --> 00:13:26,470
Your house is ready. You will be satisfied.

135
00:13:27,330 --> 00:13:30,320
Hey. Get Song-yi home safely.

136
00:13:32,120 --> 00:13:35,200
Cheon Song-yi really didn’t know that?

137
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:36,590
Isn’t the post for fun?

138
00:13:36,590 --> 00:13:39,280
Cheon Song-yi is known for her ignorance.

139
00:13:39,280 --> 00:13:44,160
Teachers have a dinner party tonight, you know?

140
00:13:44,160 --> 00:13:46,830
Everyone is asked to go for it.

141
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:50,770
Mr. Do Min-joon,

142
00:13:50,770 --> 00:13:52,400
will you come?

143
00:13:55,910 --> 00:13:58,320
Mr. Do Min-joon,

144
00:13:59,950 --> 00:14:01,940
the dinner party, will you…

145
00:14:01,940 --> 00:14:03,410
No, I won’t.

146
00:14:03,820 --> 00:14:07,320
We’ve worked in one office for over a year,

147
00:14:07,320 --> 00:14:10,390
but we never have a meal together.

148
00:14:10,390 --> 00:14:13,730
Mr. Do, do you know my name?

149
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:17,530
You don’t know?

150
00:14:17,530 --> 00:14:21,390
What? You almost see each other every day.

151
00:14:21,390 --> 00:14:22,700
Then do you know mine?

152
00:14:24,180 --> 00:14:25,170
How about

153
00:14:25,170 --> 00:14:26,460
mine?

154
00:14:29,620 --> 00:14:31,230
I’m leaving now.

155
00:14:36,850 --> 00:14:40,300
Song-yi, let’s stop using SNS.

156
00:14:40,300 --> 00:14:42,030
I said no.

157
00:14:42,030 --> 00:14:45,880
I have 20,000 friends, you know?

158
00:14:45,880 --> 00:14:47,640
They are just followers,

159
00:14:47,640 --> 00:14:50,020
easily to become antis.

160
00:14:50,530 --> 00:14:54,900
Garlic pizza event happened just a month ago.

161
00:14:54,900 --> 00:14:59,720
Dear all, garlic pizza has a garlic taste.

162
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:01,650
Am I the only one thinks it’s strange?

163
00:15:01,650 --> 00:15:04,560
You were despised by many people

164
00:15:04,560 --> 00:15:06,880
for not knowing garlic’s meaning.

165
00:15:06,880 --> 00:15:08,650
It won’t be a problem if you don’t post text.

166
00:15:08,650 --> 00:15:12,030
Many texts make people feel awkward.

167
00:15:12,030 --> 00:15:14,570
We’ve got a large amount of malicious comments.

168
00:15:14,570 --> 00:15:16,940
I don’t care about the malicious comments.

169
00:15:16,940 --> 00:15:18,030
Song-yi,

170
00:15:18,300 --> 00:15:22,180
let me get this straight.

171
00:15:22,180 --> 00:15:26,160
You can’t chat with the fans by yourself.

172
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:29,080
It makes you ridiculous.

173
00:15:29,530 --> 00:15:33,120
It’s better for you to keep mystery.

174
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:34,580
Shut your mouth and drive the car.

175
00:15:45,740 --> 00:15:47,210
Stop following me.

176
00:15:47,210 --> 00:15:49,160
But you don’t know where your home is.

177
00:15:49,160 --> 00:15:50,090
Why not?

178
00:15:50,090 --> 00:15:52,620
You think I can’t find my home just because
I was confused by garlic?

179
00:15:52,620 --> 00:15:54,110
The room number is 2301, right?

180
00:15:54,110 --> 00:15:56,470
You are right. But we can’t leave you alone.

181
00:15:56,470 --> 00:15:57,570
Let me send you upstairs.

182
00:15:57,570 --> 00:15:58,840
No, thanks.

183
00:15:58,840 --> 00:15:59,610
Song-yi…

184
00:15:59,610 --> 00:16:01,500
Enough, I will go upstairs on my own.

185
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:02,950
The earrings…

186
00:16:02,950 --> 00:16:05,700
We have to return it to the sponsor.

187
00:16:13,890 --> 00:16:15,090
Is it okay?

188
00:16:15,660 --> 00:16:17,220
Can I leave now?

189
00:16:20,890 --> 00:16:22,820
It really doesn’t matter?

190
00:16:22,820 --> 00:16:24,830
She met a psycho

191
00:16:24,830 --> 00:16:27,770
in the elevator last time.

192
00:16:28,160 --> 00:16:30,910
You didn’t see what the psycho suffered?

193
00:16:30,910 --> 00:16:33,720
He was beaten with her bag

194
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:35,670
into a jelly.

195
00:16:35,670 --> 00:16:39,110
Honestly, I felt sorry for a psycho.

196
00:17:27,210 --> 00:17:28,680
Hey.

197
00:17:30,340 --> 00:17:32,110
Why don’t you press it?

198
00:17:32,780 --> 00:17:36,450
I mean the floor.

199
00:17:39,110 --> 00:17:43,910
Yes, I’m Cheon Song-yi.

200
00:17:43,910 --> 00:17:46,590
When did you begin to follow me?

201
00:17:50,070 --> 00:17:53,990
How can you get my address so quickly?

202
00:17:57,870 --> 00:18:00,640
What do you want? Sign for you?

203
00:18:00,640 --> 00:18:03,620
Or will you leave if I take a photo with you?

204
00:18:06,690 --> 00:18:11,040
You look young. I know youth are energetic.

205
00:18:11,040 --> 00:18:13,780
But you’d better focus on studying at your age.

206
00:18:13,780 --> 00:18:16,650
Or you can take exercises to release yourself.

207
00:18:16,650 --> 00:18:19,320
If you follow me with some dirty thoughts,

208
00:18:19,320 --> 00:18:21,180
you’d better stop now.

209
00:18:21,180 --> 00:18:24,720
I’ve dealt with this kind of things before.

210
00:18:25,840 --> 00:18:27,420
You psycho!

211
00:18:27,420 --> 00:18:31,110
Hey! Are you going to my house? Hey! Where…

212
00:18:31,110 --> 00:18:36,350
Damn! A neighbor?

213
00:18:37,300 --> 00:18:40,190
You live here?

214
00:18:40,190 --> 00:18:43,840
I moved here today. 2301.

215
00:18:43,840 --> 00:18:45,500
I scared you just now?

216
00:18:49,030 --> 00:18:51,710
You really don’t know

217
00:18:51,710 --> 00:18:53,890
who I am?

218
00:18:53,890 --> 00:18:55,060
Should I know?

219
00:18:55,060 --> 00:18:58,550
No, I didn’t mean that.

220
00:18:59,740 --> 00:19:01,510
But why are you looking at me?

221
00:19:01,510 --> 00:19:03,960
I’m going to press the password.

222
00:19:05,210 --> 00:19:08,880
Sorry! Sorry!

223
00:19:17,140 --> 00:19:21,700
Why did he treat me like that?

224
00:19:22,370 --> 00:19:24,360
He really doesn’t know me?

225
00:19:24,360 --> 00:19:26,100
It’s impossible.

226
00:19:26,100 --> 00:19:27,980
Is he from North Korea

227
00:19:27,980 --> 00:19:30,230
or another world?

228
00:19:30,230 --> 00:19:34,660
Everyone in South Korea knows Cheon Song-yi.

229
00:19:34,660 --> 00:19:39,100
Even nobodies can be called national actors.

230
00:19:39,100 --> 00:19:42,840
Only actors known across the country

231
00:19:42,840 --> 00:19:45,390
can be called national actors.

232
00:19:45,390 --> 00:19:51,190
It’s ridiculous
if he is known with only several works.

233
00:19:51,190 --> 00:19:55,950
National actors should be
as popular as Cheon Song-yi is.

234
00:19:56,660 --> 00:20:00,900
All our children were underage stars.

235
00:20:00,900 --> 00:20:04,760
But now only Song-yi and Se-mi are still stars.

236
00:20:04,760 --> 00:20:07,880
Song-yi has a new soap opera, right?

237
00:20:07,880 --> 00:20:12,140
Yes. Director Bong wants to work with her.

238
00:20:12,140 --> 00:20:14,660
It’s hard to reject it.

239
00:20:14,660 --> 00:20:16,310
Hope she can do a good job.

240
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:21,640
Oh. Se-mi will act together, right?

241
00:20:21,640 --> 00:20:24,450
Really? It’s not mentioned in the report.

242
00:20:24,450 --> 00:20:26,200
No big deal.

243
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:28,840
She seems to act as a friend of Song-yi.

244
00:20:28,840 --> 00:20:30,940
News only refers to the leading role.

245
00:20:30,940 --> 00:20:32,420
Oh.

246
00:20:32,420 --> 00:20:36,830
Song-yi moved today. Don’t you help?

247
00:20:36,830 --> 00:20:39,720
What? Moving?

248
00:20:39,720 --> 00:20:44,690
So you don’t know your daughter moved today?

249
00:20:47,440 --> 00:20:51,510
Of course I know

250
00:20:51,510 --> 00:20:53,710
she moved into her new house today.

251
00:20:53,710 --> 00:20:55,450
I intended to help.

252
00:20:55,450 --> 00:20:59,780
But she let me take a break and didn’t allow.

253
00:20:59,780 --> 00:21:01,750
Where is her new house?

254
00:21:03,960 --> 00:21:06,680
It’s Seocho-dong.

255
00:21:06,680 --> 00:21:09,970
Gold Apartment in Daechi-dong.

256
00:21:11,190 --> 00:21:14,910
Yes. I know it’s Daechi-dong.

257
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:19,890
It’s a slip of the tongue.

258
00:21:28,280 --> 00:21:29,700
Please stop.

259
00:21:33,870 --> 00:21:36,270
Get on. Let me send you back.

260
00:21:36,270 --> 00:21:37,500
No, thanks.

261
00:21:37,500 --> 00:21:39,590
You’d better get a driving license.

262
00:21:39,590 --> 00:21:42,530
Or you can ask Song-yi for a driver.

263
00:21:42,530 --> 00:21:44,570
It now looks miserable.

264
00:21:45,470 --> 00:21:49,460
Song-yi tried to have a driver for me,

265
00:21:49,460 --> 00:21:53,670
but I refused because I don’t want to bother.

266
00:21:53,670 --> 00:21:55,970
It’s easy to take a taxi.

267
00:21:55,970 --> 00:21:59,200
Well. Keep safe.

268
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:01,340
Okay, thank you. Bye.

269
00:22:06,730 --> 00:22:12,100
How can she act rich
